subSubSection.paragraph:
There are several sources on 

Bos taurus

basicranial anatomy (
Sisson, 1911
; 
Getty, 1975
; 
Schaller, 1992
), but in some cases the terminology differs from that used in contemporary comparative anatomy and paleontology works (
Wible, 2003
; 
Giannini et al., 2006
; 
O’Leary et al., 2013
) and many key structures are not labeled. The description here is based on 
two adult
specimens: the bulla in situ is based on SBU-MAR 15 (fig. 12), and the bulla removed is based on SBU-MAR 14.
